  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nWhen sending a sticker, the message object includes a \"fallback\" text to display in case the receiving status version is too old to support stickers. Something along the lines of \"please update to the latest version to see a nice sticker here\".\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nThe language of the message is selected based on the locale of the sender. When sending a sticker from a phone with a German locale, the included fallback message is \"Aktualisiere auf die neueste Version, um hier einen sch√∂nen Sticker zu sehen!\". This allows the receiver of the sticker to deduct private information (nationality, location) about the sender.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe message is sent in English always and then localized at the receiving end.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nThe message is localized by the sender, thereby leaking metadata.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Open Status on a device with a locale other than English\r\n2) Add sticker pack\r\n3) Open Status in emulator\r\n4) run re-frisk\r\n5) Send sticker from device with non-English locale\r\n6) look at the message text in the debugger\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
